<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="76" pageNumber="77">
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Malaconothridae" genus="Trimalaconothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="optatus">Trimalaconothrus optatus</taxonomicName>
(Berlese, 1908)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="76" pageNumber="77">
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Malaconothridae" genus="Malaconothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="optatus">Malaconothrus optatus Berlese</taxonomicName>
, 1908, p. 12; 1910, p. 223, pl. 19 fig. 46.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="76" pageNumber="77">
Berlese described (1908) and figured (1910) 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Malaconothridae" genus="Malaconothrus" genus.bestMatchDistance="33" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="optatus">M. optatus</taxonomicName>
as having two claws at each leg; probably the smaller median claw had been overlooked, for afterwards (Berlese, 1916b, p. 336) the species was added to 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Malaconothridae" genus="Trimalaconothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Trimalaconothrus</taxonomicName>
, characterized by tridaetylous legs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="76" pageNumber="77">
The description is, however, insufficient and no specimens are present in the Berlese Collection, so that the identity of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Malaconothridae" genus="Trimalaconothrus" genus.bestMatchDistance="106" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="optatus">T. optatus</taxonomicName>
is uncertain. The indication of the type locality (&quot;Italia&quot;) is of no value.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
